#BonesBrigade, these guys are still riding the same incredible wave of skate inspiration they hopped on decades ago. 
- Q&A Panel all rider + George and Stacy. 
- Custom B.B. artwork on display.
- Hosoi, who was almost on the Brigade but fate had a different plan, talking with Lance. 
- Fans eagerly awaiting.
- Tony Signing a Postcard for me.
- The only household name I’d want my photo with. 
- First time meeting Lance, told him the 1st time I saw him was on Sk8TV doing a grip tutorial. He called himself the Martha Stewart of skateboarding. 
- Legends on stage and in the audience, Jeremy Wray. 
- By far the longest line because of the time he took with each guest, always gracious and sincere, Mr Mullen. Told him how much I loved his Plan B parts, he humbly deflected and spoke about Duffys part, great person. 
- Just me and Johnny Rad.

Thank you so much to @transworldskate for letting me share my humble little skate hoard and putting together a really great edit. I was just thrilled to do this little show and tell with some of my stuff with people who care. It posted today on their YouTube channel so check it out if you can 🙏. (It’s so unnerving to talk on camera, so go easy on me.) Thank you guys for being my friends here on Instagram all these years.
